        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix: apply humanDelay between Telegram streamed block replies (Resolves #68945)",
        "body": "Fixes #68945.\n\nThe Telegram block-streaming path does not wire `resolveHumanDelayConfig(cfg, agentId)` into `dispatchReplyWithBufferedBlockDispatcher`, so `agents.defaults.humanDelay` / per-agent `humanDelay` overrides have no effect on Telegram block replies.\n\nThis change matches the pattern already in Slack, Discord, Signal, iMessage, Matrix, MS Teams, Feishu, Tlon, and Mattermost: import `resolveHumanDelayConfig` through the existing `bot-message-dispatch.agent.runtime.ts` seam and pass its result as `dispatcherOptions.humanDelay` in `bot-message-dispatch.ts`.\n\n## Test plan\n- [x] `pnpm test extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-dispatch.test.ts` (74 passed, including new `forwards configured humanDelay to the block dispatcher` case)\n",
